From nigel allen Subject Results of GUSTO Heart Attack Study to be Released Friday Here is a press release from Medical Science Results of GUSTO Heart Attack Study to be Released Friday To Assignment Desk Medical Writer Contact Jim Augustine of Medical Science Communication or Steve Hull or Tracy Furey or April or Marriott News Advisory Results of the largest heart attack study ever undertaken the Global Utilization of Streptokinase and t PA for Occluded Coronary Arteries trial GUSTO will be presented Friday April at the Clinical Research A press conference will be held at GUSTO evaluates the most aggressive emergency room treatment strategies available to clear blocked heart arteries and restore blood flow to the heart a process called The thrombolytic strategies compared in GUSTO use powerful drugs to break up blood clots in heart vessels quickly and prevent clots from These strategies have never been compared directly in a large scale clinical trial until The results are expected to have an important impact on heart attack treatment The press conference will be held at two locations live at the National Press Club Main Lounge Floor Washington and via satellite at The Hotel Macklowe Street Floor New York City between Broadway and GUSTO results will be presented by Eric Topol GUSTO Study Chairman professor and chairman of the Department of Cardiology at The Cleveland Clinic Foundation Robert Califf clinical director GUSTO Coordinating Center and Associate Professor of Medicine at Duke University Medical Center and Allan Ross coordinator of the GUSTO Angiographic Substudy and professor and director of the Division of Cardiology at The George Washington University Medical Editorial Notes Attention television The press conference may be viewed in its entirety via satellite starting at EDT C band Telestar Transponder dual audio or Transponder Following the press conference there will be a news package and b roll Camera ready illustrations also will be available at the 